# Run Vader Analysis on each tweet and find the average sentiments - NYT
nyt_compound_list = []

nyt_negative_list = []

nyt_text_counter = []

# Loop through all tweets
for tweet in public_tweets_nyt["statuses"]:

    # Run Vader Analysis on each tweet
    compound = analyzer.polarity_scores(tweet["text"])["compound"]
    pos = analyzer.polarity_scores(tweet["text"])["pos"]
    neu = analyzer.polarity_scores(tweet["text"])["neu"]
    neg = analyzer.polarity_scores(tweet["text"])["neg"]

    # Add each value to the appropriate array
    nyt_compound_list.append(compound)
    nyt_positive_list.append(pos)
    nyt_negative_list.append(neg)
    nyt_neutral_list.append(neu)
    
    # Add to counter
    counter = counter + 1
    nyt_text_counter.append(counter)
    
nyt_summary2_data = {"Source Account": nyt_source_acct, "Text": nyt_tweet_text, "Date": nyt_create_date,
                "Compound Score": nyt_compound_list, "Positive Score": nyt_positive_list, "Negative Score": nyt_negative_list,
